== Potatoes ==

Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch pieces; place in a large #pot with enough
@water{} to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to #pot.

Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

== Vegetables and Herbs ==

While potatoes cook, trim and quarter @button mushrooms{8%ounce} (skip if your
mushrooms are pre-sliced!).

Trim, peel, and finely dice @carrots{6%ounce}. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(halved and diced).

Strip half the @thyme{¼%ounce} leaves from stems (all the leaves for 4); mince leaves.

== Filling ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably ovenproof, #pan
over medium-high heat. Add @diced yellow onion{1}(diced), @ground turkey{10%ounce},
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until
browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a
paper-towel-lined plate. Carefully discard any excess grease from pan.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan over
medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until lightly browned, ~{5%minutes}.

Add another drizzle of olive oil to pan, then stir in carrots, diced onion,
and salt. Cook, stirring, until veggies are softened, ~{5-7%minutes} more.

Use pan used for beef or turkey here.

Stir @butter{1%tablespoon} into same pan, then add thyme, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon},
and @flour{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, ~{1%minute}. Stir in @tomato paste{1%unit}
until incorporated.

Add @water{3/4%cup} and @veggie stock concentrate{3}, scraping up browned bits.
Bring to a boil; reduce to a low simmer and cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture to a baking dish now.

After adding stock concentrates, stir in beef or turkey. Cook through the rest
of this step, adding splashes of water if filling seems too thick.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

Mash drained potatoes with @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, half the cheddar cheese,
and @butter{3%tablespoon} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved
potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Heat broiler to high.

Once filling has thickened, spoon mashed potatoes on top; spread in an even
layer, leaving a 1-inch border around edge of baking dish.

Sprinkle mashed potatoes with remaining @white cheddar cheese{½%cup}.

Broil shepherd's pie until cheese is lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Let rest at least ~{5%minutes}, then divide between plates and serve.